Add `android:filterTouchesWhenObscured`

title: Add `android:filterTouchesWhenObscured`
message:
Add `android:filterTouchesWhenObscured`

To prevent tapjacking like attacks we should explicitly enable this attribute. Fore more details see https://blog.lookout.com/look-10-007-tapjacking/

Note that this does not affect all Android devices as for example Samsung started with Ice Cream to mitigate this issue on OS level.

To test this I can recommend the https://github.com/mwrlabs/tapjacking-poc application.

Replace Log.wtf calls with Log.e

title: Replace Log.wtf calls with Log.e
message:
Replace Log.wtf calls with Log.e

This will prevent crashing when running on a userdebug phone. Log#wtf
should only be used when the program can not go on because a critical
assertion fails. These all don't seem to meet that criteria.

Fixes #1603

Commit for the PR

The pull request targets:

	1) Introduces Gradle support
	2) Updates maven support (even thou the apk generated is not
stable)
	3) Updates the setup_env.* scripts to support different building
tools
	4) Removes non UTF-8 characters
	5) Removes switches on R.id entries (not supported anymore from
ADT >= 14)
	6) Introduced a binary dependency (.aar) that replace the actionbarsherlock
sub-module

Remainders:

	1) Change the sub-module back to the owncloud android library
once the PR will be merge

title: Commit for the PR
message:
Commit for the PR

The pull request targets:

	1) Introduces Gradle support
	2) Updates maven support (even thou the apk generated is not
stable)
	3) Updates the setup_env.* scripts to support different building
tools
	4) Removes non UTF-8 characters
	5) Removes switches on R.id entries (not supported anymore from
ADT >= 14)
	6) Introduced a binary dependency (.aar) that replace the actionbarsherlock
sub-module

Remainders:

	1) Change the sub-module back to the owncloud android library
once the PR will be merge

message:
Add code to handle ownCloud servers running on IDN

ownCloud instances can run on servers having an internationalized domain
name. This commit adds a conversion function between ASCII and Unicode.
The conversion function is used in the Authenticator and Preferences
activities.

See issue #469.
